## ARCHITECTURE CORRECTION (v5.1)

### Two User Roles

| Role | Access |
|---|---|
| **Contest Creator** | Create contests, configure rounds, set bot configs per round, view all student scores, publish results |
| **Contestant (Student)** | Browse contests, join, code, test locally, submit final code |

### Bots: Private Market Simulator — NOT Leaderboard Participants

Bots exist ONLY inside each student's **private isolated simulation session**.
They create a realistic dynamic market so the student's code is not just
paper-traded against a static replay — but they are INVISIBLE to other students
and do NOT appear on the leaderboard.

```
Student A's Session:          Student B's Session:
┌──────────────────────┐      ┌──────────────────────┐
│  Student A's LOB     │      │  Student B's LOB     │
│  + Bot Fleet (priv.) │      │  + Bot Fleet (priv.) │
│  → A's PnL score     │      │  → B's PnL score     │
└──────────────────────┘      └──────────────────────┘
        ↓                               ↓
   ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │  LEADERBOARD: A's PnL% vs B's PnL%    │
   │  (students only, bots never appear)    │
   └────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

