## 0. What This Platform Is

An algorithmic trading contest. Contestants submit a Python trading algorithm.
The platform runs that algorithm against a live Limit Order Book (LOB) populated
by 5 intelligent bot strategies that react dynamically to the contestant's trades.

**The point:** A bot that doesn't react is just expensive data replay. Our bots
see the contestant's orders in the LOB and respond like real market participants.
A good contestant algorithm must handle spread widening, momentum piling, and
mean reversion resistance — because the bots enforce all three.

```
 Contestant Algorithm (Python → compiled .so)
         │
         │ sees live LOB ← bots have already responded to your last move
         ▼
 ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 │            LIVE PERSISTENT LOB                    │
 │  (accumulates across all 1,000,000 ticks)         │
 │                                                   │
 │  ← Bot 1: Market Maker  (posts quotes, reacts)   │
 │  ← Bot 2: Momentum      (follows your moves)     │
 │  ← Bot 3: Mean Reversion (fades your moves)      │
 │  ← Bot 4: Noise Trader  (random realistic flow)  │
 │  ← Bot 5: Sniper/Arb   (anchors price to signal) │
 └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
         ▼
 Fills distributed → Contestant PnL updated → Leaderboard
```

**Scoring:** Primary = PnL at end of simulation. Secondary = avg latency/tick.
Equal PnL → lower latency wins. Negative PnL → ranked below all positive.

