## 1. The Tick Loop — Core Architecture (Revised)

Every tick, this exact sequence executes on Core 2:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  GAME MASTER — PER TICK SEQUENCE                 │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 1: Read price signal for tick T                            │
│    signal = tick_dataset[T]  // {mid_price, volatility, news}   │
│    ~4ns — L1 cache hit, hugepage                                 │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 2: Snapshot current LOB state                              │
│    snap = lob.snapshot()                                         │
│    // {best_bid, best_ask, depth[10], last_trade, spread}        │
│    ~8ns — L1 cache (LOB hot path fits in 24KB)                   │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 3: Compute ALL bot orders INLINE (C++, same core)          │
│    for bot in [mm, momentum, mean_rev, noise, sniper]:           │
│        bot.compute(snap, signal)  → pending_orders[]            │
│    ~10ns total for all 5 bots (compiled C++, branchless)         │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 4: Write LOB state + prev fills → rendezvous               │
│    Regular stores (NOT NT) into shared struct                    │
│    ~15ns                                                          │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 5: Signal contestant (release store on gm_sequence)        │
│    ~4ns                                                           │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 6: Spin-wait for contestant response (100µs deadline)      │
│    _mm_pause loop on sb_sequence                                 │
│    Watchdog thread monitors — SIGKILL child on TLE               │
│    Contestant computation time NOT counted in platform overhead  │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 7: Read contestant orders from rendezvous                  │
│    ~4ns — L1 cache hit                                            │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 8: Process ALL orders into LOB                             │
│    a) Bot orders (arrive first — same core, ~0ns transport)      │
│    b) Contestant order (arrives after response signal)           │
│    LOB.process_all(pending_orders) → fills[]                    │
│    FIFO matching within same price level                         │
│    ~10ns (branchless, best-ptr fast path)                        │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 9: Distribute fills                                        │
│    contestant_fills = fills.for(CONTESTANT_ID)                   │
│    for bot: bot.notify_fill(fills.for(bot.id))                   │
│    ~5ns                                                           │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 10: PnL update (fixed-point, __int128 for safety)          │
│    pnl += contestant_fills.value(snap.mid_price)                 │
│    ~3ns                                                           │
│                                                                   │
│  Step 11: Telemetry                                              │
│    __rdtscp → tsc_delta                                          │
│    _mm_stream_si64() × fields → telemetry ring                   │
│    _mm_sfence()                                                   │
│    ~26ns                                                          │
│                                                                   │
│  TOTAL PLATFORM OVERHEAD (excl. contestant compute): ~89ns/tick  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
